



Revision of C and C++

Here’s a quick revision of C & C++ (easy to memorize + examples) 👇

🔹 C Language Revision
1. Basics
C is a procedural language (step-by-step execution)

Structure: main() is the entry point

Example:

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    printf("Hello");
    return 0;
}
2. Data Types
int, float, char, double

Example:

int a = 10;
float b = 5.5;
char c = 'A';
3. Control Statements
if, else, switch, loops (for, while)

Example:

if(a > 5) {
    printf("Greater");
}
4. Functions
Reusable block of code

Example:

int add(int x, int y) {
    return x + y;
}
5. Arrays & Strings
Store multiple values

Example:

int arr[3] = {1,2,3};
char str[] = "Alok";
6. Pointers
Store address of variable

Example:

int a = 10;
int *p = &a;
7. Structure
User-defined data type

Example:

struct student {
    int id;
};
🔹 C++ Revision
1. OOP Concepts
Class & Object

Example:

class Student {
public:
    int id;
};
2. Encapsulation
Data + methods in one unit

3. Inheritance
One class uses another

Example:

class A {};
class B : public A {};
4. Polymorphism
Same function, different behavior

Example (Function Overloading):

int add(int a, int b);
float add(float a, float b);
5. Constructor
Automatically called when object created

Example:

class A {
public:
    A() {
        cout << "Constructor";
    }
};
6. Difference (C vs C++)
C	C++
Procedural	Object-Oriented
No classes	Classes available
No inheritance	Supports inheritance
🔹 Quick Memory Trick
C = Functions + Pointers + Structure

C++ = C + OOP (Class, Inheritance, Polymorphism)

